reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 31, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great fans! They seem very high quality
reviews.reviewText: I am retrofitting an older case with an updated motherboard and decided along the way that it needed 3 new fans, too. Did some searching and settled on these. They showed up quickly, seem very solid, have a nice cover to go on the inside so no one (me!) sticks a finger or anything in them while they're running. I have a fan controller and they all seem to play nicely together. Very happy with this choice!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 11, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Absolute quiet for Ham Radio / CB / Audio gear.
reviews.reviewText: Grear for Hi-Fi audio equipment and Ham Radio / CB equipment. I installed one in each of my two 13.8VDC ham shack power supplies using super velcro to secure the fan to the chassis and I installed a LM7810 voltage regulator. Running at 10 volts from the added regulator the fan in each of my power supplies runs inaudible while still moving plenty of air. The cover (not pictured) has been modified to allow inlet air on the side.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars This fan is virtually silent!
reviews.reviewText: I am somewhat disappointed in this fan. It is advertised as being variable speed depending on the voltage. Input voltage between 5v-12v. I had hoped to be able to control the speed of this fan using a PWM controller. I realize this is not the intended use for this fan, because the PWM controller does not actually vary the voltage but rather the duty cycle of the negative lead. but I was hopeful because another reviewer stated he was using his in this manner. It did not work. In fact I had to turn the POT on the controller all the way up before the fan would move at all. Turning down the POT even slightly and the fan shuts off. I'm not going to give the fan a low mark because it did not function as I had hoped, because I understand it was never intended to be used in this fashion. I will say the fan is very quiet and seems to push a fair amount of air. But I will probably be sending it back because it doesn't function any differently than the fan I'd hoped to be replacing.
